# Slide Content Filtering — Walkthrough

## What Was Done

Added a 3-layer intelligent filtering pipeline to prevent AI summary and quiz generation on non-educational slides (title pages, contact info, exam dates, etc.).

### Files Changed

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| [content_filter.py](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/content_filter.py) | **[NEW]** 3-layer pipeline: heuristic → density scoring → LLM-as-a-judge |
| [file_parse_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/file_parse_service.py) | Integrated filter into PDF parsing; metadata slides skip AI processing |
| [ai_content.py](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/api/ai_content.py) | Added pre-check to `/generate-summary` and `/generate-quiz` endpoints |
| [ai_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Osama/ascend-academy/backend/services/ai_service.py) | Updated prompts to explicitly ignore metadata content |

### How It Works

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Slide Text] --> B{Layer 1: Heuristic}
    B -->|METADATA| D[Skip AI → empty summary/quiz]
    B -->|EDUCATIONAL| E[Full AI Processing]
    B -->|UNCERTAIN| C{Layer 2: Density Score}
    C -->|Low density| D
    C -->|High density| E
    C -->|Borderline| F{Layer 3: LLM Judge}
    F --> D
    F --> E
```

